    public interface TypeKey
extends java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TypeKey>, IEnumValue, IGosuObject
    Version:
    Jul 31, 2002 2:49:21 PM

    The TypeKey class serves as a discrete entry in a typelist. It contains all of the information found in the metadata about that key, such as its id, code, name, description, and priority. It also contains a pointer to the list that it belongs to so that that list can be referenced, the name can be obtained, other TypeKeys of the same sub-type can be obtained, etc.

    Author:
    mshaw
